UTTERANCE.TRANSLATION: '"Today is the last day of the semester right?" "No next week is. We still have one more week of class."'
'"The book you read was really good." "No, it was lousy I didn't like it."'
'"Did your roommate get arrested last night?" "No, I was at breakfast this morning he/she was fine."'
'"Texas has a good football team." "No they have a lousy team and they are losing. They haven't won a game yet."'
'"Tomorrow is Sunday." "No, today is Thursday which means tomorrow is Friday."'
'"Your mom will love the surprise party." "No, my mom hates surprises."'
'"No matter what the weather is, the baseball game will go on." "Well, yes, but if there is a hurricane it will be cancelled."'
'"Hey last night John Stewart interviewed Sarah Jessica Parker." "No, he didn't interview her he interviewed Sarah Palin."'
'"Rick Perry is a Mormon." "No, Mitt Romney is a Mormon, not Rick Perry."'
'“The economy now is great! It`s fine.” “No! It`s really messed up now.”'
'"The cafeteria is serving ice cream tonight." "No, I just came from there and there wasn't any ice cream."'
'"Did you vote for George Bush?" "No, I wasn't even old enough to vote when he ran for office."'
'"Did someone finally find your umbrella?" "No, it's still missing."'
'"Your uncle lives in a big house right?" "No, he lives in a small apartment."'
'"Hey, I may be late for the movie." "No, it's fine, you have time; the movie starts at 10pm."'
'"You're going to Hawaii for Christmas break ?" "No, I'm going to Hawaii for Spring break."'
'"Mc Donalds is a snobby restaurant right?" "No, Mcdonalds is a cheap restaurant. They serve hamburgers."'
'“Mayor Bloomberg is around six feet tall or more.” “No, he`s short; he`s maybe five feet six inches, that`s all.”'
'"Mary is a vegetarian isn't she?" "No, she had a bbq last month."'
'"Did you finish your homework." "No, I haven't even started yet.'
'"You're going to run in the Boston Marathon right?" "No I haven't ran and I don't plan on starting"'
'"The table over there has a book that someone left." "No there is no table over there or a book."'
'"There's no homework for History class right?" "No, we have homework, We have to write a three page paper."'
'"Today I went out and the weather was lousy." "No, it's beautiful and warm outside. It's perfect."'
